UPDATE 2024;
At certain times the game still shows room for improvement, such as minor stutters on the more populated and open areas of Koboh. However, performance has been vastly improved since the release. If you haven't picked this up yet, I'd highly recommend it now. It's rare we get such a well crafted story with meaningful gameplay these days, especially from Star Wars. Survivor builds on everything good from the 1st game and makes it even better, while also introducing new elements to combat that create even more enticing (and addicting) possibilities. May the force be with you Jedi friends!
ORIGINAL UPON RELEASE;
The game itself is amazing, what a fantastic sequel. However the optimization for the PC version is horrible. Riddled with performance issues from stuttering gameplay, to crashing and freezing your computer. EA claims windows 10 is the issue, but I'm running 11 on a rather high end build and am forced to run medium graphics settings just to get passable performance between crashes(60ish frames on a 1440p 240ghz monitor and a 3090). I'm impatient and wanted to see where Cal's adventure led him, but if you're more disciplined than I then wait for a patch jedi friends.
